.TH "tpm2_pcr_read" 9 "tpm2_pcr_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm2_pcr_read \- read a PCR value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tpm2_pcr_read
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u32 pcr_idx "  ","
.BI "struct tpm_digest *digest "  ","
.BI "u16 *digest_size_ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
TPM chip to use.
.IP "pcr_idx" 12
index of the PCR to read.
.IP "digest" 12
PCR bank and buffer current PCR value is written to.
.IP "digest_size_ptr" 12
pointer to variable that stores the digest size.
.SH "RETURN"
Same as with tpm_transmit_cmd.
